rComments: Jeremy was one of the best TAs I have ever had.  He was genuinely concerned about every student, and he helped each one as much as they needed it.  He was very down to earth, and made argumentation one of my most memorable courses at the U of I.
Pretends he cares about you but doesn't.
Great Teacher You will learn a lot about the subject from him. Great readings and assignments. He is not fake and I don't recall him ever talking about his own research. Highly recommended.
This guy is kind of fake.  He acts like he wants to be everyone's buddy, but I don't think he really cares about anyone learning anything.  He talks about his own research too much.

Jeremy is one of the nicest people that I have ever met.  Not only does he have respect for his students, but he respects their time and effort.  I would reccomend him to anyone, no matter what class he's teaching.  He'll make it fun and worthwhile, I promise.

He is truly one of the best teachers that I've had at this school. Jeremy is so easy to talk to and is a very intelligent person. Seriously, anyone would love this class. He really cares about all of his students and would do anything to help them. Plus...he's not too bad on the eyes.
